tourBios.exmtStatus: Conditionally Exempt: 24th qualifier from Qualifying Tournament, Money List 61-100
tourBios.carHigh: Played on the Dakotas Tour from 2007-12 and recorded six wins...Worked as the assistant golf professional at Plantation GC in Bismarck, N.D. 2012: Debuted on the Web.com Tour at the Cox Classic but missed the cut...Victories came at The Dakotas Tour at Pine Hill GC, The Dakotas Tour at Oxbow CC and Emerald Hills, Arnolds Park, Iowa. 2011: Won twice on The Dakotas Tour, The Dakotas Tour at Marshall GC and The Dakotas Tour at Westward Ho CC. 2010: Picked up one win on The Dakotas Tour, at Brooks National GC.
tourBios.otherCarHigh: Had one win in college, at the University of Louisiana-Monroe...Was a four year letterman in golf at Bismarck High School in North Dakota.
tourBios.personal: Favorite pro teams are the Atlanta Falcons and the Miami Heat...Twitter account is @timkunick...Would like to trade places with Justin Timberlake for a day...Never travels without his toothbrush...Favorite golf memory was playing with his brother at age 8...Lists Spyglass Hill as his favorite golf course...Favorite professional sports teams include the Atlanta Falcons and Miami Heat...Would like to trade places for a day with Justin Timberlake...Enjoys reading, fishing and hunting.

dyn.dynResults: His best finish on the Web.com Tour was T34th in 2013 at the Mexico Championship Presented by Banamex.
